    "Signs of opioid intoxication include pinpoint pupils (miosis), drowsiness, slurred speech, impaired attention, and respiratory depression. Withdrawal symptoms include dysphoria, muscle aches, lacrimation, rhinorrhea, pupillary dilation (mydriasis), piloerection (gooseflesh), yawning, diarrhea, nausea/vomiting, fever, and insomnia. Unlike alcohol withdrawal, opioid withdrawal is rarely life-threatening but extremely uncomfortable. Behavioral signs include doctor shopping, social withdrawal, financial problems, and needle marks (if injecting).",
